Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
dd_get(25.10)                                                    dd_get(25.10)

Name
       dd_get - Returns OpenAccess library information

Syntax
       dd_get

        {-all_lib}  |{-dd <dd_objHandle> | -lib <libName> | -cell {<lib cell>}
       | -cellview {<lib cell view>} }

        [-children | -file | -path | -type |-name]}

       Returns OpenAccess library information.

Parameters
       -all_lib
              Returns a list of design data (dd) object handles for  the  list
              of libraries present in the library definition file ( cds.lib).

       -cell {<lib cell>}
              Specifies the names of the library and cell to be processed.

       -cellview {<lib cell view>}
              Specifies  the  names  of  the  library,  cell,  and  view to be
              processed.

       -children
              Returns the dd object handles of the children of  the  specified
              dd  object  handle. Children of libraries are cells. Children of
              cells are views.

       -dd <dd_objHandle>
              Specifies the dd object to be processed.

       -file  Returns the dd object handles of all the files in the  specified
              dd object handle.

       -lib <libName>
              Specifies the name of the library to be processed.

       -name  Returns the name of the specified dd object handle.

       -path  Returns  the  absolute  path name (dd path) of the specified  dd
              object handle.

       -type  Returns the type of the specified dd object handle.

Examples
              * The  following  command  returns   the   path   of   the   li-
                brary/cell/view as shown below:

                dd_get -cellview {pdkLib cell1 abstract} -path

                returns:

                /libs/pkdLib/cell1/abstract

                This command is equivalent to the following SKILL function:

                ddGetObjReadPath(ddGetObj("pdkLib" "cell1" "abstract"))

              * The  following proc traverses the cds.lib structure (expanding
                #INCLUDE as required) to get the complete list  of  OpenAccess
                libraries and their full paths:

                #  expand #INCLUDE as needed and print all libraries and their
                full paths

                proc print_all_lib_paths {} {

                    puts [format "%16s -> %s" "Library Name" "Library Path"]

                    puts
                "----------------------------------------------------------------"

                    foreach oa_lib [dd_get -all_lib] {

                        puts [format "%16s -> %s" [dd_get -dd  $oa_lib  -name]
                [dd_get -dd $oa_lib -path]]

                    }

                }

